Product Inventory Management System – Python Documentation
1. Introduction
A Product Inventory Management System is a software application developed using Python to manage and track product stock in a store or warehouse. The system allows users to add products, update stock, remove products, and view inventory details.
The main goal of this system is to simplify inventory tracking and reduce manual errors.
2. Objectives
To maintain product records efficiently
To track product quantity in stock
To add, update, and delete products
To display inventory information easily
To reduce manual inventory management
